The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                    
	 Arnab Nandy has been retained as the Bengal U-22 captain for their next CK Nayudu Trophy match against Hyderabad starting on November 3. Shreevats Goswami, who led the U-22 side against Punjab has been inducted in place of Pankaj Shaw but selectors decided to persist with Nandy, who was the captain in the match against Uttar Pradesh.                
	 The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) has appointed Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) treasurer Subir Ganguly as their observer for the fourth ODI between India and Australia to be held at Mohali on Monday.                
	 Adrija Bramhachari and Srija Neogy entered the cadet girls final of the BM Chattoraj Memorial Table Tennis Championship organised by SKDTTA. Ritika Kundu will clash with Monomita Biswas in the nursery girls final.                                                                                                                                                                        
